  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "01604c3e-cc69-46d7-9261-bab2a7f5a6c4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This creates a table with 3 rows and 1000 columns. But maybe we want instead a df with 3 columns and 1000 rows. We can create a df with one array, and then add more columns. Read more about making dfs here: https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/reference/api/pandas.DataFrame.html."
   ]
  },
