   "source": [
    "More often than not, you will probably want to load in data from a text or csv file. Let's use a an example data using real data from one of Dr. John Salzer's emission-line galaxy surveys! \n",
    "\n",
    "Reading in data files directly to a dataframe can be done with the `read_csv` function. \n",
    "\n",
    "Data in text files can be \"delimited\" or spearated in few different ways, most commonly: spaces, tabs, and commas. This input file is delimited by spaces, so we can set the delimiter key to '\s+' "
   ]
