   "source": [
    "We can merge two data frames together using the `merge` function. We can use the keyword argument \"on\" to specify what column we want to merge everything on. By setting \"on\" to KISSR, we are telling pandas to grab all of the information from both dfs associated with a given value in the \"KISSR\" column and place it into one row in the new df. Read more about merging dfs here: https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/reference/api/pandas.DataFrame.merge.html."
   ]
  },
