   "source": [
    "Say we want to pass our df through a function we have defined. Since this is a photometry df, let's use a color index as an example. \n",
    "\n",
    "Let's find the g - r color for all of our galaxies. First, we define a function called `find_color`, which takes in two magnitudes, subtracts them, and outputs the color. We can apply this function to our df by converting the relevant columns to numpy arrays with the method `to_numpy` and setting the dtype to `float`, and we can store the result in a new column called \"g-r.\""
   ]
  },
