   "source": [
    "Sometimes, we may want to sort our df based on a certain column. We can use the `sort_values` method to do this. The main key we need to set is the \"by\" key. By default, pandas sorts from smallest to largest with \"ascending\" key. When we are sorting by columns with numbers, it is best to set `key=pd.to_numeric`.` This tells pandas that the dtype of your column is a float.  \n",
    "\n",
    "Read more about `sort_values` here: https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/reference/api/pandas.DataFrame.sort_values.html."
   ]
  },
